The initiation of anaphase and exit from mitosis depend on a multi-subunit ubiquitination complex called the anaphase-promoting complex (APC)1 or cyclosome. Later in anaphase and telophase the APC promotes the inactivation of the mitotic cyclin-dependent protein kinase 1 by ubiquitinating its activating subunit cyclin B.
